column2: [{u'PolicyName': u'S3Access', u'PolicyDocument': {u'Statement': [{u'Action': u's3:*', u'Resource': {u'Fn::Join': [u'', [u'arn:aws:s3:::', {u'Ref': u'S3Bucket'}, u'/*']]}, u'Effect': u'Allow'}]}}, {u'PolicyName': u'IAMAccess', u'PolicyDocument': {u'Statement': [{u'NotAction': u'iam:*', u'Resource': u'*', u'Effect': u'Allow'}]}}, {u'PolicyName': u'EC2Access', u'PolicyDocument': {u'Statement': [{u'Action': u'ec2:*', u'Resource': u'*', u'Effect': u'Allow'}]}}]

Existing S3 bucket to use for Jenkins backups and restores

{u'Fn::Base64': {u'Fn::Join': [u'', [u'#!/bin/bash -xe
', u'# Helper function
', u'function error_exit
', u'{
', u'  cfn-signal -e 1 -r "$1" '', {u'Ref': u'WaitHandle'}, u"'
", u'  exit 1
', u'}
', u'/opt/aws/bin/cfn-init --stack ', {u'Ref': u'AWS::StackName'}, u'    --resource LaunchConfig', u'    --configsets install', u'    --access-key ', {u'Ref': u'HostKeys'}, u'    --secret-key ', {u'Fn::GetAtt': [u'HostKeys', u'SecretAccessKey']}, u'    --region ', {u'Ref': u'AWS::Region'}, u" || error_exit 'Failed to run cfn-init'
", u'# Post-cfn work
', u'# Updating to Java 8
', u'yum install -y java-1.8.0-openjdk.x86_64 || true 
', u'sudo /usr/sbin/alternatives --set java /usr/lib/jvm/jre-1.8.0-openjdk.x86_64/bin/java || true
', u'sudo /usr/sbin/alternatives --set javac /usr/lib/jvm/jre-1.8.0-openjdk.x86_64/bin/javac || true 
', u'yum remove java-1.7 || true 
', u'sudo wget -O /etc/yum.repos.d/jenkins.repo http://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.repo
', u'sudo rpm --import http://pkg.jenkins.io/redhat-stable/jenkins.io.key
', u'yum install -y jenkins
', u'sudo mkdir -p /var/lib/jenkins
', u'sudo chown -R jenkins:jenkins /var/lib/jenkins
', u"# Handle case where cron doesn't detect the new /etc/cron.d file
", u'#service cron restart
', u'# Attempt to restore from backup
', u'export AWS_CONFIG_FILE=/etc/aws.conf
', u'sudo /usr/local/bin/jenkins-restore s3://', {u'Ref': u'S3Bucket'}, u'/', {u'Ref': u'S3Prefix'}, u' /var/lib/jenkins || true # ignore errors
', u'sudo service jenkins start
', u'sudo chown -R jenkins:jenkins /var/lib/jenkins
', u'sudo chmod -R 755 /var/lib/jenkins
', u'# Start Jenkins
', u'sudo service jenkins restart
', u'sudo chkconfig jenkins on
', u'sleep 400
', u'printf "Subject: Your Jenkins Password

', u'$(cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword)
', u'CHANGE THIS RIGHT AWAY AT: ', u'http://', {u'Ref': u'DnsRecord'}, u'" | sendmail -v ', {u'Ref': u'EmailAddress'}, u'
', u'# All is well, signal success
', u'./opt/aws/bin/cfn-signal --exit-code 0 --reason "Stack setup complete" '', {u'Ref': u'WaitHandle'}, u"'
", u'#EOF']]}}

{u'Fn::Join': [u'\n', [u'#!/bin/bash -e', u'', u'USAGE="Usage: $0 S3_TARGET JENKINS_HOME\\n', u'\\n', u'Example:\\n', u'$0 s3://mybucket/jenkins/jenkins-201405011901.tar.gz /var/lib/jenkins\\n', u'\\n', u'If S3_TARGET is a directory, restore from the newest file. Make sure to include the trailing slash:\\n', u'$0 s3://mybucket/jenkins/ /var/lib/jenkins"', u'', u'S3_TARGET=$1', u'JENKINS_HOME=$2', u'if [[ -z "`echo $S3_TARGET|grep \'^s3://\'`" ]]; then', u'    echo -e $USAGE', u'    exit 1', u'fi', u'', u'if [[ "$S3_TARGET" == */ ]]; then', u"    S3_TARGET=$S3_TARGET`aws s3 ls $S3_TARGET|tail -1|awk '{print $NF}'`", u'fi', u'', u'LOCAL_BACKUP=/tmp/`basename $S3_TARGET`', u'aws s3 cp $S3_TARGET $LOCAL_BACKUP', u'', u'rm -rf $JENKINS_HOME', u'#if [[ -d "$JENKINS_HOME" ]]; then', u'#    read -p "Delete existing $JENKINS_HOME? (y/n) " -n 1 -r', u'#    echo', u'#    if [[ $REPLY =~ ^[Yy]$ ]]; then', u'#        rm -rf $JENKINS_HOME', u'#    else', u'#        echo "Bailing out"', u'#        exit 1', u'#    fi', u'#fi', u'', u'mkdir -p $JENKINS_HOME', u'tar zxf $LOCAL_BACKUP -C $JENKINS_HOME', u'rm -f $LOCAL_BACKUP']]}

{u'Fn::Join': [u'\n', [u'#!/bin/bash -e', u'', u'USAGE="Usage: $0 JENKINS_HOME S3_TARGET\\n', u'\\n', u'Examples:\\n', u'$0 /var/lib/jenkins s3://mybucket/jenkins/jenkins-201405011901.tar.gz"', u'', u'JENKINS_HOME=$1', u'S3_TARGET=$2', u'if [[ -z "`echo $S3_TARGET|grep \'^s3://\'`" || ! -d "$JENKINS_HOME" ]]; then', u'    echo -e $USAGE', u'    exit 1', u'fi', u'', u'LOCAL_BACKUP=/tmp/`basename $S3_TARGET`', u'', u'tar -C $JENKINS_HOME -zcf $LOCAL_BACKUP .\\', u'    --exclude "config-history/" \\', u'    --exclude "config-history/*" \\', u'    --exclude "jobs/*/workspace*" \\', u'    --exclude "jobs/*/builds/*/archive" \\', u'    --exclude "plugins/*/*" \\', u'    --exclude "plugins/*.bak" \\', u'    --exclude "war" \\', u'    --exclude "cache"', u'', u'aws s3 cp $LOCAL_BACKUP $S3_TARGET', u'rm -f $LOCAL_BACKUP']]}
